Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says South Africa is willing to assist in scientific research being conducted in Madagascar, looking into a herbal remedy to combat COVID-19. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said South Africans must realise the seriousness of COVID-19 and continue to observe measures to protect themselves. Mkhize said social distancing is key. READ: South Africa's COVID-19 death toll climbs to 148 The minister expects an influx of COVID-19 patients in the coming weeks. He said more field hospitals and beds are needed. Mkhize was speaking at a handover ceremony in Rustenburg on Wednesday, where a massive consignment of personal protective equipment was handed over from Sibanye Stillwater and Old Mutual. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.